		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>den 12 <add>&#63;</add> May <hi rend="underline">1849</hi></date></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><addressee>Mr I Leeser Rev.</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p><persName role="author">Nathan Ottinger</persName> <add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p><placeName>Pitt street No 87</placeName>.</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p>Minister of the congregation of Mikveh&#61;<lb/><placeName>Israel</placeName></p>
			<p><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> May&#44; 1849</date>.</p>
			<p>Mr. <sic>J.</sic> <addressee>Leeser Rev.</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">Although</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><del>?</del> I have already sold a<lb/> good many of your prayer books &#8220;Dibrei Zadikim&#8221;&#44; which I have ob&#45;<lb/>tained from <persName>Mr. Goldstein</persName>&#44; I sold them at a very small profit. It is generally known that it is possible to obtain the same prayer<lb/> books in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> at &#36;2.&#44; while until now I have had to pay<lb/> <persName>Mr. Goldstein</persName> &#36;2.25. I therefore take the liberty to drop you these<lb/> lines in order to inquire whether I could not have them at a lower<lb/> price either from you or through you&#44; so that I might be able to<lb/> compete against every other tradesman. In that event I should<lb/> certainly be able to use more of them. I should also like to know<lb/> the price of our <sic>Pentatuechs</sic> and other books. With regard to this<lb/> please answer me in the near future. As to my character&#44; please<lb/> inquire of <persName>Mr. Isaacs</persName>&#44; or anyone else in this town.</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">With best wishes&#44; and sincerely&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Nathan Ottinger</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">&#40;Scribe and Book&#45;seller&#41;</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>Pitt St. No. 87</placeName></p>

          
        </body>
